2. Concrete issues, however, are more easily resolved but only if they have
                        been well prepared and the Soviets do not have to contend with surprises
                        that have not been aired by the collective leadership;

4. Meeting the “people” is of little interest to the Soviets. Their
                        preoccupation is with those who have the power of decision (this,
                        incidentally, is why Congressional delegations do so poorly in the USSR);
